<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920305-0059</DOCNO><DOCID>920305-0059.</DOCID><HL>   Justices to Hear Key Case   On Abortion Next Month</HL><DATE>03/05/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><IN>LAW AND LEGAL AFFAIRS (LAW)</IN><NS>LAW andamp; LEGAL ISSUES AND LEGISLATION (LAW)</NS><GV>SUPREME COURT (SUP)</GV><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)PENNSYLVANIA (PA)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   WASHINGTON -- The Supreme Court said it would hear oralarguments in a potentially critical abortion-rights caseApril 22.   The announcement yesterday, which had been expected, meansthat a decision is likely to be issued by early summer -- intime to make abortion a central issue at both the Republicanand Democratic national conventions.</LP><TEXT>   The case involves a challenge to a Pennsylvania law thatimposes a number of restrictions on women seeking abortions,including a requirement that they tell their husbands oftheir intentions.   The high court could use the case as an opportunity tooverturn Roe vs. Wade, the 1973 decision that recognized aconstitutional right to abortion. But the justices coulduphold the Pennsylvania law without explicitly reversing Roe.</TEXT></DOC>